            <abstract encodinganalog="520" label="Abstract"> The Lockridge mss. II, 1941-1975,
                consist primarily of correspondence from author Ross Franklin Lockridge, Jr.,
                1914-1948, to various individuals. The Lilly Library acquired these letters to
                complement the manuscript files for Lockridge's book, <title render="italic">
                    Raintree County.</title> Many of the letters discuss the success of <title render="italic">Raintree County</title> as well as Lockridge's untimely
                death.</abstract>
        </did>

